If this were so, the expedition might be regarded as a success Tor Caesar dedicated a breastplate which purported to be made of British pearls to Venus Genetrix in her temple. Pliny (N. H. ix. 5116) notices however that they were small and of a bad colour. Tacitus also depreciates the British . pearls, calling them ‘somewhat dark and livid².'
